post_text: I know we haven’t checked in much lately - partly because we were grieving a bit over missing our people and partly due to trying to meet new needs arising from this. Blessings to Providence Baptist and Monticello Presbyterian for helping to meet those emergencies. Through their donations we are helping with paper goods and face masks. We are connecting older folks and those with disabilities to the food bank and some are receiving emergency meals from Meals on Wheels and NEGA AAA. We are even available to run essential errands if they don’t have other means. So proud of our staff for assuring they have the highest quality of meals possible thru this - about 80 meals a day are being delivered even though we are shut down. We are checking of our “older weekly to assure their safety. We have a wonderful community and so many are helping others. We thank a local industry who donated 60 meals for Easter to help out a restaurant who is struggling. We are so blessed thru all of this!

post_text: We sure miss all of our folks! While in shut down we are still delivering about 80 meals a day. We are helping those who need it with grocery shopping. We are also collecting toilet paper donations for our home bound. If you would like to donate please drop items off between 8am and 3pm Monday-Thursday. Honk and we will pick it up. We have a great community! So thankful to live here!
